[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T19:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/black_ops_6_piano_puzzle.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The <strong>piano puzzle</strong> is one of the earlier mysteries you\u2019ll come across in the <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/call-of-duty-black-ops-6/443261\">Black Ops 6</a></em> campaign.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Found on the way to the training area on the safehouse\u2019s ground floor, you\u2019ll have to find a hidden code to play the piano, which, in turn, will lead to more secrets to solve.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">This <em>Black Ops 6</em> guide offers an explainer on how to figure out the piano puzzle, as well as an explicit piano puzzle solution.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-b", "id": 1383905, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/black-ops-6-guides/469805/piano-puzzle-solution-how-solve", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to solve the piano puzzle in Black Ops 6", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T19:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/VXMA_S3_FG_00002318_Still012-2_3000.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">When adapting hours and hours of actual play, the cast and crew of <em>The Legend of Vox Machina </em>had to make some changes. Some are <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/critical-role/466215/legend-vox-machina-percy-cast-death-episode-7\">hugely emotional arcs</a> crafted from originally smaller moments, while others are a chance to pull in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/critical-role/463196/legend-vox-machina-exandria-unlimited-calamity-crossover\">lore that evolved years</a> after the original run.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">And in the case of the season finale, it was a chance for one cast member to make amends for a spur-of-th", "id": 1383906, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tv/468601/legend-vox-machina-season-3-ending-scanlan-change", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Vox Machina season 3 finale lets a cast member say sorry", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T16:57:03+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24842142/OVR_FlashpointGameplay_India_003.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">As promised, Blizzard Entertainment is going to give <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/23385539/overwatch-2-review-battle-pass-free-to-play-blizzard-entertainment\">Overwatch 2</a></em> players one thing they\u2019ve been asking for over the past two years: <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24205547/overwatch-2-6v6-update-blizzard\">a return to 6v6 team compositions</a>. The rollout of 6v6 play in December will be part of a series of tests, <a href=\"https://overwatch.blizzard.com/en-us/news/24151413/director-s-take-continuing-the-6v6-discussion/\">game director Aaron Keller said Thursday</a>, that \u201care all about ", "id": 1383191, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/470043/overwatch-2-6v6-test-season-14-start-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Blizzard\u2019s bringing back 6v6 Overwatch 2 in December to see how that whole thing goes", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T16:30:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/ve3_dtlr1_dtlr2_itlrABCDE_stringout_4k_rec709_full-Copy-0153_2000x838_thumbnail.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/469476/venom-3-the-last-dance-tom-hardy-knull\">The third movie in Sony and Tom Hardy\u2019s Venom trilogy</a> has arrived in theaters, but it isn\u2019t really clear what\u2019s next for the series. Like most superhero movies these days, <em>Venom: The Last Dance </em>doesn\u2019t expressly answer that question during its initial runtime \u2014\u00a0it\u2019s set up as closure for the trilogy that started with <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2018/10/2/17929870/venom-movie-review-tom-hardy-sequel-potential\">2018\u2019s <em>Venom</em></a>. But no one ever dies permanently in comics, and it\u2019s rare for a ", "id": 1383192, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/marvel/469466/venom-last-dance-post-credits-scenes-sequel", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Venom: The Last Dance\u2019s post-credits scene is all about the future", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T16:20:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Kris from Deltarune walking across the street. \" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Toby Fox/8-4\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/deltarune.jpeg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The release schedule behind <em>Deltarune</em>, the next big RPG created by <em>Undertale</em> developer Toby Fox, is a bit confusing. In <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2018/10/31/18044640/deltarune-free-download-undertale-game\">fall of 2018</a>, Fox and his team released the first section of the game for free. Roughly three years later, he <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/22691556/deltarune-chapter-2-review-toby-fox-undertale\">surprise-released Chapter 2</a> of the game and said that his team would release more of the game down the line. However, delivering on that initial promise has been slow", "id": 1383193, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/465334/deltarune-when-will-chapter-3-release-date-undertale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Everything we know about Deltarune, Toby Fox\u2019s follow-up to Undertale\u00a0", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T16:15:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25256534/44__823_.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/23287600/prey-review-predator-hulu\">Prey</a></em>, 20th Century Studios\u2019 revival of the Predator franchise in its post-Disney-acquisition, played like gangbusters when it hit Hulu in 2022. A year later, Polygon spoke to director Dan Trachtenberg, who admitted <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23906146/prey-2-sequel-director-dan-trachtenberg-prey-4k\">the stakes were staggeringly high</a> for what felt like an inevitable sequel \u2014 so he didn\u2019t want to just crank out <em>Prey 2</em>. Instead, as announced in February, Trachtenberg and 20th Century would jump from the 18th century to the far future i", "id": 1383194, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/movies/470022/second-predator-movie-release-date-2025", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A second secret Predator movie is coming out next year\u00a0", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T15:11:35+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Alan-Wake-2-The-Lake-House-Control-2-TEASER.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/23932094/alan-wake-2-review-ps5-xbox-series-x-pc\">Alan Wake 2</a></em>\u2019s recently released downloadable content, <em>The Lake House</em>, has strong ties to developer Remedy Entertainment\u2019s other ongoing franchise, Control. The DLC sends players into a Federal Bureau of Control research facility as agent Kiran Estevez to unravel its secrets and battle new enemies. <em>The Lake House</em> isn\u2019t just more connective tissue for the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23961028/remedy-connected-universe-mcu-alan-wake-2-control\">Remedy Connected Universe</a>, it appears to include an explicit teaser to", "id": 1382820, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/469880/control-2-teaser-alan-wake-2-dlc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Alan Wake 2\u2019s new DLC has a big, exciting Control 2 Easter egg", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T15:02:10+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/14318542/Good_Omens_Official_Image_NYCC.FNL_2.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23808742/good-omens-season-2-minisodes-neil-gaiman\">Good Omens</a></em> will return to close out its story of an angel and demon against the world, <a href=\"https://deadline.com/2024/10/good-omens-to-end-90-minute-episode-neil-gaiman-exits-1236157372/\">reports Deadline</a>, with creator Neil Gaiman and his production company, Blank Corporation, exiting the production. Amazon Video paused production on a third season of the joint Amazon/BBC series in early September, following the publication of <a href=\"https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/neil-gaiman-two-more-w", "id": 1382821, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tv/469910/neil-gaiman-good-omens-s3-movie", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Neil Gaiman exits Good Omens, which will wrap up with a 90-minute TV movie", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T14:15:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A photo shows a Steam Deck on a pink table.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Photo: Amelia Holowaty-Krales/Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/236920_Polygon_Steam_Deck_AKrales_0106.webp?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">If you\u2019ve got some holiday travel coming up, you might need a portable battery to keep your devices charged when you\u2019re away from an outlet. Whether you have a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/what-to-buy/23627961/best-steam-deck-accessories\">Steam Deck</a>, a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/what-to-buy/23592426/best-nintendo-switch-accessories\">Nintendo Switch</a>, a phone, or a tablet (or perhaps some combination of that lineup), you shouldn\u2019t settle for a battery that\u2019s low on charging speed or capacity. This blue-colored Baseus battery has both, packed with ", "id": 1382439, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/good-deals/469809/fast-portable-battery-amazon-baseus-steam-deck-switch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This speedy, Steam Deck-ready portable battery is almost half off", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/inzonem10Ssilenthill2lowstand.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Just as 27-inch 1440p OLED gaming monitors are catching on with more PC gamers thanks to a steady reduction in price, Sony is throwing a curveball with its first OLED monitor, the $1,099.99 InZone M10S. The M10S retains the unparalleled contrast and stellar picture quality that OLED is known for, but rather than join the ranks with the commonly used 240 Hz refresh rate, it\u2019s raising the bar with 480 Hz instead.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The increased refresh rate is the M10S\u2019 distinguishing hardware feature, and it\u2019s a big selling point if you\u2019re a competitive PC gamer who wants cutting-edge tech to improve your performance. (The 0.03-millis", "id": 1382440, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/review/469727/sony-inzone-m10s-oled-pc-ps5-gaming-monitor", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sony&#8217;s first OLED gaming monitor is fast, but not the right fit for most gamers", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Mintrocket, LocalThunk/Nexon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/0b01afb3524b635442567101c8a0e0408a6922cf.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Here\u2019s a video game crossover that\u2019s pretty cool: You can actually play a version of indie card game <em>Balatro</em> in <em>Dave the Diver</em>. It makes sense: Dave is already in <em>Balatro</em>. It\u2019s only natural for <em>Balatro</em> to come to the fishing and restaurant management simulator.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The version of <em>Balatro</em> found in <em>Dave the Diver</em> is playable underwater in the Sea People Village, where it\u2019s referred to as <em>Jimbo\u2019s Game </em>\u2014 a nod to the joker in <em>Balatro</em>. It\u2019s not common for a game crossover to actually put another game inside t", "id": 1381946, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/469837/balatro-dave-the-diver-cyberpunk-stardew-valley-crossover", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can play Balatro in Dave the Diver", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T12:20:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"GTA Online promo art for Halloween Encounters\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Rockstar Games\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/GTA-Online-10242024-7.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>The weekly <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gta-online-guides\"><em><strong>GTA Online</strong></em></a><strong> update for October 24, 2024</strong>, is live with reward events, discounts, prizes, and haunted vehicles.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>GTA Online </em>weekly update guide will tell you everything happening in Los Santos this week.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"tqxGpX\"><strong>GTA Online special events</strong></h2>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">As Halloween continues, spooky season is ramping up in <em>GTA Online</em>. Watch out for <st", "id": 1381540, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gta-online-guides/469740/october-24-weekly-update-events-haunted-vehicles", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "GTA Online update for the week of October 24", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/VXMA_S3_FG_00002801_Still015_3000.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">If you can\u2019t get Scanlan Shorthalt\u2019s tawdry songs out of your head as you watch <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/critical-role/466215/legend-vox-machina-percy-cast-death-episode-7\">The Legend of Vox Machina</a></em>, we have great news for you: the full soundtrack for the third season of <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/critical-role/463196/legend-vox-machina-exandria-unlimited-calamity-crossover\">The Legend of Vox Machina</a></em> will be available on Oct. 25. And in addition to Neal Acree\u2019s orchestral score, the album contains a number Scanlan\u2019s original songs (as performed by Sam Reigel) with Peter Habib of Mr. Fantastic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p ", "id": 1381541, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/critical-role/469032/legend-vox-machina-soundtrack-exclusive-scanlan", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Hear the first track from Vox Machina season 3&#8217;s banger-filled soundtrack release", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T11:22:23+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/image-3.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Google\u2019s famous doodles \u2014 the illustrations that show up in place of the Google logo nearly every day \u2014 have been known to take the form of surprisingly great games on occasion. Today\u2019s doodle is no exception: <em><a href=\"https://doodles.google/doodle/rise-of-the-half-moon/\">Rise of the Half Moon</a></em> is a strategy card game that celebrates the half moon point in October\u2019s lunar cycle.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Each three-level playthrough starts with an empty 3&#215;3 board connected by vertical and horizontal lines. Your hand consists of three random moon phase cards, and on your turn, you can place a card on the board. The aim is to pair matching cards, p", "id": 1381065, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/impressions/469741/google-doodle-rise-half-moon-lunar-cycle-strategy-game", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Thursday\u2019s Google Doodle is actually a really fun strategy game", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-24T10:40:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/u